Attributions
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This project is an independent, from-scratch set of native ports inspired by and
kept behaviorally compatible with Excalidraw. It is not affiliated with or
endorsed by the Excalidraw project. "Excalidraw" is the name of the upstream
project by its respective authors.

  Excalidraw — https://github.com/excalidraw/excalidraw
  Licensed under the MIT License.

The hand-drawn rendering re-implements the algorithms of the following libraries.
The web client depends on the upstream npm packages directly; the Swift
(RoughKit / FreehandKit) and Kotlin (rough-kotlin / freehand-kotlin) clients are
independent re-ports validated for numeric/visual parity against them:

  Rough.js — https://github.com/rough-stuff/rough
  Copyright (c) 2019 Preet Shihn. Licensed under the MIT License.

  perfect-freehand — https://github.com/steveruizok/perfect-freehand
  Copyright (c) 2021 Stephen Ruiz Ltd. Licensed under the MIT License.

